Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the 13th Annual National Catholic Prayer Breakfast in Washington, D.C. In his remarks, Pence expressed his condolences for the recent terror attacks in London and Melbourne. He discussed his Catholic upbringing and the influence of his faith on his life. Pence highlighted the contributions of Catholic Americans to the fabric of American life and praised their dedication to serving others. He also emphasized President Donald Trump's support for religious liberty, persecuted Christians around the world, and the pro-life movement. Pence urged attendees to continue standing up for their beliefs and to pray for America's healing and unity.